Where did the Apollo 11 mission land back on Earth?

context: Apollo 11 left lunar orbit and returned to Earth, landing safely in the <a1_0>Pacific Ocean<a1_0/> on <a0_0>July 24, 1969<a0_0/>. When the spacecraft splashed down, 2,982 days had passed since Kennedy's commitment to landing a man on the Moon and returning him safely to the Earth before the end of the decade; the mission was completed with 161 days to spare. With the safe completion of the Apollo 11 mission, the Americans won the race to the Moon.
